result.execSummary:
The defendant was charged with both OWI (5th or 6th) [Modifiers: Penalty - Operating While under the Influence (5th+ Offense)] and Operating w/ PAC (5th or 6th) [Modifiers: Penalty - Operating While under the Influence (5th+ Offense)]. The defendant was found guilty of OWI (5th or 6th) [Modifiers: Penalty - Operating While under the Influence (5th+ Offense)] and the other charge, Operating w/ PAC (5th or 6th) [Modifiers: Penalty - Operating While under the Influence (5th+ Offense)] was dismissed by the court.

  • Curt E Shields was found guilty of OWI (5th or 6th) [Modifiers: Penalty - Operating While under the Influence (5th+ Offense)], a class H felony, Wisconsin Statutes 346.63(1)(a).
  • Curt E Shields was found guilty of Bail Jumping-Felony, a class H felony, Wisconsin Statutes 946.49(1)(b).

Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

Cases heard: 14CF86 & 13CF450, Defendant Curt E Shields in court with attorney Amanda K Riek.  Crystal N Long appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Court went over the rights & elements. Defendant plead no contest to count 1&2 in 14CF86 and count 1 in 13CF450. Court found defendant guilty, entered judgment in 14CF86, sentence: 4 yr. prison, consisting of 1 yr. confinement, consec. to 13CF450, 3 yr. extended supervision, $1,694 fine, 36 mo. revocation, 36 mo. IID, complete AODA, follow treatment recommendations, not possess/consume alcohol, submit DNA sample, $250 DNA surcharge. Not eligible for Challenge, is eligible for EER.  2 days jail credit on ct. 1. Ct. 2, sentence withheld, defendant placed on 2 yr. probation, consecutive to prison sentence, $518 costs, not possess/consume alcohol. Posted bond applied. In 13CF450, 4 yr. prison, consisting of 1 yr. confinement, 3 yr. extended supervision, commence forth with, $1,694 fine, 36 mo. revocation, 36 mo. IID, complete AODA, follow all treatment recommendations, submit DNA sample, pay $250 DNA surcharge, not possess/consume alcohol. 3 days Jail credit. Cts. 3-4 in 14CF86 read in and dismissed. Ct. 5 dismissed outright. Ct. 2 in 13CF450 dismissed. Not eligible for Challenge, is eligible for EER.
